Privacy Policy
At Vanguard, your privacy is our top priority. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our bot.

1. Information We Collect
We only collect essential information needed for bot functionality, such as your Discord user ID, server data, and preferences. We do not collect personal data such as emails or passwords.

2. Data Usage
The information we collect is used solely to provide the features and services of Vanguard, including moderation, protection, and server management. We will never sell, share, or trade your information with third parties.

3. Data Storage
All collected data is stored securely and used solely within the context of our botâ€™s operation. We take strong measures to ensure that your information is protected from unauthorized access.

4. Cookies
Vanguard does not use cookies or track your activity outside the bot's functionality. The bot does not engage in any form of tracking or data collection beyond what is necessary to function within Discord.

5. Data Retention
We retain your data only as long as necessary to maintain your preferences and the functionality of Vanguard. If you decide to stop using Vanguard, we will remove your data from our system.

6. Your Rights
You have the right to request access to your data, correct any inaccuracies, or delete your data at any time. To exercise these rights, please contact us via the support channels listed in the bot.

7. Updates to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted in this repository, and your continued use of Vanguard indicates acceptance of those changes.

By using Vanguard, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy. If you have any questions or concerns, feel free to contact us through our support channels.
